# Known divergence: error/notice cursor offset only ("at character N"). NOT a
# multigres bug. multigateway rewrites the submitted query text before
# forwarding it to PostgreSQL (parse + deparse), which shifts the byte offset
# PostgreSQL records for an error/notice cursor. The message text, ordering, and
# every result row are byte-identical to stock PostgreSQL; only the trailing
# "at character N" position differs. This patch records that offset shift so the
# test is verified against multigres's deparsed-query cursor positions.
--- a
+++ b
@@ -166,12 +166,12 @@
 #1305.1|POINT(10 10)
 #1305.2|t
 #1305.3|t
-ERROR: MultiPolygon cannot contain MultiPoint element at character 8
-ERROR: MultiLineString cannot contain MultiPoint element at character 8
-ERROR: MultiPoint cannot contain MultiPoint element at character 8
-ERROR: CompoundCurve cannot contain MultiPoint element at character 8
-ERROR: MultiCurve cannot contain MultiPoint element at character 8
-ERROR: MultiSurface cannot contain MultiPoint element at character 8
+ERROR: MultiPolygon cannot contain MultiPoint element at character 13
+ERROR: MultiLineString cannot contain MultiPoint element at character 13
+ERROR: MultiPoint cannot contain MultiPoint element at character 13
+ERROR: CompoundCurve cannot contain MultiPoint element at character 13
+ERROR: MultiCurve cannot contain MultiPoint element at character 13
+ERROR: MultiSurface cannot contain MultiPoint element at character 13
 #1453.1|t
 #1453.2|f
 #1454|t
